DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0022-1996(87)80008-9
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022199687800089
AB  - This paper analyzes the process of trade and capital-account liberalization in a Keynesian framework with unemployed resources. Previous studies on this subject have ignored the potential interactions between the liberalization process and the pre-existing distortions in the economy. This paper derives the optimal liberalization policy (given the Keynesian context) and solves for explicit formulas for the import tariffs and the capital-account tax in a two-period general equilibrium model. It is argued that a trade reform is likely to have recessionary effects in the short run if the capital account has already been liberalized.
