AB  - This paper stresses the effects of currency substitution and speculation on inflation hedges on the relative price of home goods in the two-sector general equilibrium portfolio balance model. Examining the overshooting hypothesis of exchange rates in association with the overshooting phenomenon of price of inflation hedges, it has shown that exchange rate undershooting is plausible with the significant overshooting of the price of inflation hedges when domestic residents hold only domestic money and inflation hedges. However, the impact of currency substitution is strong enough to lead to exchange rate overshooting if the domestic residents have access to foreign currency.
