T1  - Trade policy and its impact on quality of imports
AU  - Analysis, A Welfare
AU  - Das, Satya P.
AU  - Donnenfeld, Shabtai
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 23
IS  - 1
SP  - 77
EP  - 95
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/08/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0022-1996(87)80006-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022199687800065
AB  - This paper examines the role of trade policies in influencing a foreign monopolist's decision on price, quantity and, in particular, the quality of its product. We show that a specific tariff leads to higher quality, whereas an ad-valorem tariff usually does the opposite. Quotas and specific tariffs are shown to be equivalent, and both dominate an ad-valorem tariff in terms of welfare. We also show that subjecting imports to minimum quality requirements hampers national welfare. Finally, we present a comprehensive ranking of all the policy instruments considered in this paper.
